# Kryon Terminal Editor — Implementation Walkthrough

## What Was Built

A fully functional terminal-based code editor in Rust with a modular workspace architecture.

### Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    CLI["kryon-cli<br/>(entry point)"] --> TUI["kryon-tui<br/>(rendering)"]
    TUI --> Core["kryon-core<br/>(engine)"]
    CLI --> Security["kryon-security<br/>(boundaries)"]
    TUI --> Security
    Core --> Ropey["ropey<br/>(rope data structure)"]
    TUI --> Ratatui["ratatui<br/>(terminal UI)"]
    TUI --> Crossterm["crossterm<br/>(terminal I/O)"]
```

