## Features Implemented

### Core Engine (kryon-core)
- **TextBuffer**: O(log n) insert/delete/replace via ropey, line access, coordinate conversion
- **CursorSet**: Multi-cursor support with anchor/head pairs, sorted deduplication, offset adjustment
- **EditCommand**: Insert/Delete/Replace with full undo/redo support
- **CommandHistory**: Capped undo/redo stacks with automatic redo-clearing on new edits
- **EditorAction/EditorEvent**: Elm-architecture event types for all editor operations

### TUI Layer (kryon-tui)
- **Terminal setup**: Raw mode, alternate screen, mouse capture, panic recovery hook
- **Editor rendering**: Line numbers, code content, cursor positioning, vertical scrolling
- **Sidebar**: Togglable explorer panel (Ctrl+B)
- **Status bar**: File name, line/col, modified indicator, status messages
- **Key bindings**: Full keyboard mapping (Ctrl+Q quit, Ctrl+S save, Ctrl+Z/Y undo/redo, arrows, Home/End, etc.)
- **File save**: Write buffer to disk with error handling
- **Quit guard**: Double Ctrl+Q required to quit with unsaved changes

### Theme System
- **Catppuccin Mocha** (default) — warm dark theme
- **Tokyo Night** — cool-toned dark theme  
- **Dracula** — vibrant dark theme
- 15 semantic color tokens per theme

### Security (kryon-security)
- **Path validation**: Traverse-safe path resolution, workspace boundary checks, filename sanitization
- **Subprocess execution**: Safe `Command` wrapper without shell interpolation

